President Obama announced his intention to nominate and appoint several individuals to key administration posts. Joyce A. Barr is nominated for Assistant Secretary of State for Administration at the Department of State. Anne W. Patterson is nominated for Ambassador to the Arab Republic of Egypt at the Department of State. Claude M. Steele is nominated for Member of the National Science Board at the National Science Foundation. The President also intends to appoint Dottie Bennett, Catherine Bertini, Tammy Duckworth, Jodi Gillette, Debra Langford, Mathew McCollough, Ronald B. Rapoport, and Deborah A. Ryan to various administration posts. Tammy Duckworth and Jodi Gillette will continue serving in their current roles in addition to these appointments. President Obama praised the skill and dedication of these individuals and looks forward to working with them in the coming months and years.